<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-457-733  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 457 733.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 17 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI completes Telecom USA acquisition: the company is sued. (MCICommunications Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (acquisitions and mergers)Telecom*USA Inc. (cases)Communications Corporation of America (cases).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     Communications IndustryMergerCourt CasesContracts.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MCI COMPLETES TELECOM USA ACQUISITION: THE COMPANY IS SUED WASHINGTON, D.C.,andO;U.S.A., 1990 AUG 17 (NB) -- MCI and Telecom USA concluded their merger,combining the nation's fourth largest long distance company for $42 pershare, or about $1.25 billion.andP;  MCI funded the merger with cash on hand andbank debt, which it expects to repay in 3 years.andM;Separately, Communications Corporation of America of Southport, Connecticutfiled a $350 million damages action in a Washington, D.C.andP;  federal courtagainst Telecom, alleging fraud and breach of a 1989 contract.andP;  CCA had beenan agent for Telecom USA, signing up calling card customers for its longdistance telephone services nationwide.andP;  The program offered charities,non-profits, and affinity groups as much as 30% of the revenue CCA would havereceived from long distance calls on Telecom USA's network.andP;  CCA alsocommitted one percent of its gross Telecom USA income to a special fund forinner city education.andM;Telecom USA notified CCA in March 1990 that it was cancelling the contract.andO;CCA says.andP;  CCA is represented by the Washington, D.C.andP;  office of the law firmBell, Boyd and Lloyd which also has offices in Chicago and Dallas.andM;An MCI spokesman said the company has not yet seen the CCA suit but willdefend against it vigorously.andP;  He added that while some Telecom USA technicalpeople may be asked to move to MCI's offices in Richardson, Texas, that won'thappen for at least 18 months.andP;  As for the marketing people, MCI has a majormarketing presence in Atlanta, he added.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19900816/Press Contact: John Houser, MCI, 800- 289-0073;William A. Duerk, for CCA, 202-466-6300)</TEXT></DOC>